F. Parking:
1. Two (2) off-street parking spaces must be provided within each manufactured home space.
2. Parking spaces shall be constructed to the standards as set forth in Article 24 Parking.
3. Off-street parking areas shall be at least four feet (4') away from any unit.
4. An applicant may utilize on-street parking if the private street within the manufactured home park is designed and constructed to accommodate on-street parking.
5. A combination of off-street and on-street parking is allowed.
llm_output.rationale: This section provides parking requirements for manufactured home parks, specifying 2 off-street spaces per manufactured home space. However, it also allows for on-street parking and a combination of off-street and on-street parking, without specifying a minimum total number of spaces per dwelling unit.
